1.title: Episode #7.1
1.plot: Stephen Mulhern hosts the eleventh series of the fun-packed companion show. As the first round of auditions gets under way, Stephen presents exclusive extra audition footage and goes behind the scenes to uncover all the latest news, views and gossip from the judges, contestants and main show hosts Ant and Dec.

2.title: Episode #7.2
2.plot: Britain's Got More Talent features backstage gossip and behind-the-scenes exclusives from one of the nation's biggest talent shows.

6.title: Episode #7.6
6.plot: Britain's Got More Talent continues its 12th series with even more post-show action. In the sixth episode, Stephen will get to know, in his own unique way, even more hilarious unseen contestants. As ever, it's these acts that make Britain's Got More Talent such compelling viewing as Stephen comes face-to-face with the unusual, the incredible and the downright outrageous.

11.title: Episode #10.11
11.plot: Throughout the live semi-finals Britain's Got More Talent will be right in the thick of it, getting all the fall-out from the results and giving viewers the opportunity to phone in and speak live to the judges straight after the main show. As always, the fun and games continue with 'Grab a Piece of Paper' live in the studio, audition challenges and even more unseen acts from this series. Stephen will be getting all the exclusive reactions and the very best gossip from the judges and behind the scenes. Plus, there'll be live music from Stefflon Don, chats with the BGT ...

-1.title: Episode dated 31 May 2017
-1.plot: Stephen Mulhern hosts the lively Britain's Got Talent companion show. Throughout the live semi-finals, Stephen gets right in the thick of it with exclusive reactions and gossip from the judges, contestants and main show hosts Ant and Dec. Famous fans of the show offer their opinions, while viewers also get the opportunity to have their say on the night's performances via phone and social media.

imdb.title: Britain's Got More Talent
plot: Some acts not seen on the main show, and more footage and interviews from those that were. Plus some relaxation time with the judges and presenters, all done with a knowing wink to the viewers.::Anonymous
